description:
The great drama of Martin Luthers life comes alive in this vivid portrayal of the penniless monks quest for trutha quest that would re-shape the church, and the world.

Martin Luther triggered a seismic upheaval that rocked the western world in the 1500swith an impact that continues to reverberate to this day. The great drama of Martin Luthers life comes alive in this vivid portrayal of the penniless monks quest for trutha quest that would re-shape the church, and the world. Perhaps the most faithful movie about Luthers life ever made, the film does not shy away from the deep theological questionsand answersthat mark Luther as one of the most influential people of the last thousand years.

Director: David Batty
Starring: Padraic Delaney, Gerharde Bode, Jr., Bruno Grzeszykowski
